Authorities believe that Nóbrega is the leader of the “Escritório de Crime,” or the Office of Crime, the militia’s tactical wing.
They were nominated by Flávio Bolsonaro, who was the only member of the assembly to vote against awarding the honor posthumously to Marielle Franco.
One of them is a colleague of the main suspect from their police academy days, according to the Civil Police report.
The car had been filled up at a gas station in Rio das Pedras on the eve of the crime.
According to an O Globo report in June, Siciliano had been accused by at least one witness of having ordered the hit against Franco, but Siciliano has vigorously denied any involvement.